      • andEtag

        public Response andEtag()
        Adds an ETag header to the response by hashing (MD5) the response body. Be aware that for every request the hash has to be generated. This will most likely increase CPU usage. See https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/HTTP_ETag
        Returns:
        A response object Response

      • end

        public Response end()
        Tells a filter that the response ends and that the request handler should not execute further filters by sending the current response to the client. This is only used within a filter.
        Returns:
        A response object Response
